        "body": "## Summary\n- Add schema-validated reviewMetrics entries to review decisions\n- Persist and render a compact Review metrics digest near PR surface stats\n- Add prompt guidance and tests for no, one, and multiple metrics\n\nFixes https://github.com/openclaw/clawsweeper/issues/191\n\n## Validation\n- tsgo -p tsconfig.json\n- tsgo -p tsconfig.repair.json\n- tsgo -p tsconfig.dashboard.json\n- node --test test/*.test.ts\n- node --test test/repair/*.test.ts dist/repair/*.test.js with local environment shims for commit signing and pnpm availability\n- coverage commands equivalent to repo check passed\n- oxfmt --check\n\n## Real behavior proof\nRan the built ClawSweeper renderer against a report fixture containing `review_metrics` front matter.\n\nCommand shape:\n\n```text\nnode --input-type=module -e \"import { renderReviewCommentFromReport } from \\\"./dist/clawsweeper.js\\\"; ... console.log(renderReviewCommentFromReport(report, \\\"none\\\"));\"\n```\n\nRelevant rendered output:\n\n```md\n**Review metrics:** 2 noteworthy metrics.\n- **Config/default surfaces changed:** 2 added, 1 changed, 0 removed. The PR introduces user-facing configuration behavior that maintainers should review before merge.\n- **Proof files affected:** 3 files affected. The PR touches proof-related code where green unit tests do not cover every runtime path.\n```\n\nThis proves the report path reads `review_metrics` front matter and renders the compact digest in the public PR review comment.",
